---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "../components/container.astro";
import Sectionhead from "../components/sectionhead.astro";
import TextAndImage from "../components/TextAndImage.astro";
import Quiz from "../components/Quiz";
import Accordion from "../components/Accordion";
import CodeSandbox from "../components/CodeSandbox.astro";
---

<Layout title="Day 2">
    <Container>
        <Sectionhead>
            <Fragment slot="title">Day 2</Fragment>
            <Fragment slot="desc">
                Web Development Tools & Interactive Learning
            </Fragment>
        </Sectionhead>
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-700 mt-20">
            <TextAndIMage
                title="foo"
                content="
In this journey, we'll be using CodeSandbox as our playground to explore HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, similar to how one experiments with Lego bricks. By mixing, matching, and reassembling these 'code bricks', we'll create interactive web projects. This playful approach allows us to understand the basics of web development while having fun, instilling a sense of creativity and exploration, just like building with Legos."
                <
                div
            >
                <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-700 mt-20">
                    <TextAndImage
                        title="Building your website like a Lego castle"
                        content="HTML (HyperText Markup Language): Imagine you're building a LEGO castle. The HTML is like the grey LEGO bricks that you use to construct the castle's walls, the towers, and the main gate. It gives the basic shape and structure to your castle."
                        imageURL="/day2/grey-bricks.png"
                    />
                </div>
                <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-700">
                    <Accordion
                        title="HTML elements used in the above page explained"
                        client:load
                    >
                        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-20">
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This declaration is not an HTML tag, but it
                                helps the browser understand that the document
                                is an HTML5 document.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;html&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This is the root of an HTML document.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;head&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This element contains meta-information about the
                                HTML document that is not displayed on the page
                                itself.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;meta&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag defines metadata about an HTML
                                document. It sets the character encoding and
                                sets the viewport for responsive design.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;title&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag specifies the title of the HTML
                                document. The title is displayed in the
                                browser's title bar or tab.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;body&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag defines the document's body, which
                                contains all the contents of an HTML document,
                                such as text, hyperlinks, images, tables, lists,
                                etc.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;header&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This element represents a container for
                                introductory content or a set of navigational
                                links.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;h1&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag defines a first-level heading. HTML
                                defines six levels of headings, with &lt;h1&gt;
                                being the highest (and generally, largest and
                                most important) level.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;nav&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag defines a section of the page with
                                navigation links.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;ul&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag defines an unordered (bulleted) list.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;li&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag defines a listSure, here is the rest of
                                the HTML table content: ```html
                                <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                    This tag defines a list item. In this case,
                                    it's used within a &lt;ul&gt; tag to create
                                    each item in the navigation menu.
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;a&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag defines a hyperlink, which is used to
                                link from one page to another. The most
                                important attribute of the &lt;a&gt; element is
                                the href attribute, which indicates the link's
                                destination.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;main&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag specifies the main content of a
                                document. The content inside the &lt;main&gt;
                                tag should be unique to the document.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;section&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag defines a section in a document. It is
                                a thematic grouping of content, typically with a
                                heading.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;h2&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag defines a second-level heading. It's
                                generally used for subheadings.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;p&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag defines a paragraph.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;footer&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This tag defines a footer for a document or a
                                section. It typically contains authorship
                                information, copyright information, contact
                                information, etc.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&amp;copy;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This is not a tag, but an HTML entity used to
                                display the copyright symbol.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </Accordion>
                </div>
                <CodeSandbox sandbox="elated-williamson-ynfx5k" />
                <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-700">
                    <Quiz client:load />
                </div>
                <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-700">
                    <hr />
                    <TextAndImage
                        title="CSS"
                        content="CSS (Cascading Style Sheets): CSS is like the instructions that tell you to put the biggest tower in the middle, the walls on the sides, and how to build a bridge at the front. It might tell you to put some green bricks at the bottom to make it look like the castle is on a grassy hill. CSS is the part that makes your castle pretty and colorful. It decides where each part of your castle goes, what color the bricks are, and how big or small they should be."
                        imageURL="/day2/crane-bricks.png"
                    />
                </div>
                <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-700">
                    <Accordion title="CSS tags explaind" client:load>
                        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-20">
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >.class</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This is a class selector in CSS. It selects
                                elements with a specific class attribute. You
                                can select multiple elements with the same class
                                name.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >#id</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This is an ID selector in CSS. It selects an
                                element with a specific id attribute. Each id
                                should be unique within a page.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >element</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This is an element selector in CSS. It selects
                                all elements of a specific type.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code
                                    class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                >
                                    {"{ property: value; }"}</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This is a CSS declaration. It consists of a
                                property and a value, separated by a colon and
                                enclosed in curly braces. The property is a type
                                of attribute of an HTML element, and the value
                                is the style applied to that attribute.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >@media</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This is a media query in CSS. It applies
                                different styles for different media
                                types/devices. For example, you can have
                                different styles for different screen sizes.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >/* comment */</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light">
                                This is a CSS comment. It is used to add notes
                                in the CSS code or to prevent the browser from
                                interpreting specific parts of the style.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </Accordion>
                </div>
                <CodeSandbox sandbox="day-1-css-forked-vh2hhs" />
                <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-700">
                    <Quiz client:load />
                </div>
                <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-700">
                    <hr />
                    <TextAndImage
                        title="JavaScript"
                        content="Now, imagine you've got some magic LEGO bricks. These magic bricks can open the castle gate when you shout 'Open Sesame!', or make the castle guards march up and down the walls. JavaScript is like these magic bricks. It makes your castle do things. With JavaScript, you can make parts of your webpage move, respond to clicks or typing, or change in any way you can imagine."
                        imageURL="/day2/magic-brick.png"
                    />
                </div>
                <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-700">
                    <Accordion title="foo" client:load>
                        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-20">
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >&lt;script&gt;</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                The &lt;script&gt; tag is used in HTML to embed
                                or reference JavaScript code.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >function changeTitle()</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This is a JavaScript function declaration.
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >document.getElementById("header-title")</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This is a JavaScript method that gets the first
                                element in the document with the id
                                "header-title".
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <code class="bg-gray-200 px-1 font-mono rounded"
                                    >.innerText = "Welcome to Your Awesome New
                                    Website!"</code
                                >
                            </div>
                            <div class="font-light mb-4">
                                This is a JavaScript property that sets the text
                                content of the specified node, and all its
                                descendants.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </Accordion>
                </div>
                <CodeSandbox sandbox="day-1-javascript-forked-dnwn7r" />
                <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 text-gray-700">
                    <Quiz client:load />
                </div>
            </TextAndIMage>
        </div>
    </Container>
</Layout>
